    • Uses of HeapDataTuple in com.gridgraph.storage.heap.tuple

      Subclasses of HeapDataTuple in com.gridgraph.storage.heap.tuple 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  EdgePrimaryDataTuple
      An EdgePrimaryDataTuple represents binary data for primary data of an edge, read from and written to file or mapped memory
      class  EdgePropertiesTuple
      An EdgePropertiesTuple represents binary data for properties data of an edge, read from and written to file or mapped memory
      class  EdgeSecondaryDataTuple
      An EdgeSecondaryDataTuple represents binary data for secondary data of an edge, read from and written to file or mapped memory
      class  HeapPropertiesTuple
      An HeapPropertiesTuple represents binary data for properties data of a graph element, read from and written to file or mapped memory
      class  VertexDegreeDataTuple
      A VertexDegreeDataTuple represents binary data for degree data of a vertex, read from and written to file or mapped memory
      Data layer for each tuple:
          int value: in degree
          int value: out degree
      class  VertexPrimaryDataTuple
      An VertexDataTuple represents binary data for data of a vertex, read from and written to file or mapped memory
      Data of an vertex is stored separately: primary data means 'first edge id', and 'property id', while secondary data means 'in-degree' and 'out-degree'
      class  VertexPropertiesTuple
      An VertexPropertiesTuple represents binary data for properties data of a vertex, read from and written to file or mapped memory
